    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Doctor Schduler Schema\n\nPatient Name, Email, Phone, Booked Date, \tBooked Time, Reason visit, Preferred/Doctor. \n\nThis smart assistant enables patients to easily schedule doctor appointments using text\n\nDoctor information and schedules are managed in Google Sheets.\n\nThe agent checks doctor availability based on up-to-date schedules.\n\nIf the selected doctor is already booked at the requested date and time, the agent alerts the patient and suggests other available time slots.\n\nIf the doctor is available, the agent confirms and books the appointment for the patient.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
        "height": 560,
        "width": 448,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "18169315-a863-4c4d-8b3d-eafe2ed4a8d1",
      "name": "Sticky Note1",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -128,
        -16
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "modelName": "=models/gemini-2.5-flash",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGoogleGemini",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -384,
        768
      ],
      "id": "2a363351-cb49-4dc9-8a5b-f3c34f5a930b",
      "name": "Google Gemini Chat Model",
      "notesInFlow": false,
      "credentials": {
        "googlePalmApi": {
          "id": "3esHT0j4BiwkzzZW",
          "name": "Google Gemini(PaLM) Api account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Stores information across the conversation, like a notepad or memory. \n\n2. In a chat, patients don’t always give all details at once. Simple Memory allows your workflow to “remember” answers (name, phone, reason) and recall them in later steps.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 224
      },
      "id": "23584c1d-932e-41be-a0d3-1600eecf20ca",
      "name": "Sticky Note2",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -704,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Understands natural language (user’s text) and extracts information (name, date, doctor, etc.) from free-form chat. \n\n2. Patients type messages in many ways (“I want to see Dr. Sharma next Monday at 10”). The AI model parses the message, figures out the intent, and picks out key info.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 208,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "9351f54d-5a84-4556-952c-34140a8b30a3",
      "name": "Sticky Note3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -448,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Creates the actual appointment in Google Calendar once all details are collected and slot is confirmed as available.  \n\n2. This is where the final booking happens. It lets the doctor see their schedule and avoids manual entry.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 208,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "a7650caa-1a0c-461a-88cf-e19d1ac48dff",
      "name": "Sticky Note4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -224,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "1. This node “wakes up” your workflow whenever a user sends a message (via chat, web, or other integrations).  \n\n2. It’s the entry point—without it, your automation would not know when a patient is trying to book an appointment. It listens for messages and starts the workflow.",
        "height": 384,
        "width": 256,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "ee433126-2025-4ca4-a416-0395da45b0f8",
      "name": "Sticky Note5",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -656,
        160
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Before booking, checks if the doctor is already busy at the requested date/time. \n\n2. Prevents double-booking and ensures the slot is truly free before confirming.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 208,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "17c12c5c-5c13-4975-bd1f-35ef3dc39f7a",
      "name": "Sticky Note6",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        16,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Sends a confirmation outlook email to the patient (and optionally the doctor) with all appointment details. \n\n2. Gives immediate feedback, acts as a record, and reassures the patient that the appointment is set.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 208,
        "color": 6
      },
      "id": "ce70686f-5c5c-45f6-a016-328ab2cff8f7",
      "name": "Sticky Note7",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        272,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Logs every booking in a Google Sheet for records, reporting, and backup.  \n\n2. Easy for admins/staff to see all appointments, export data, generate reports, or audit bookings.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 208,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "8d7849dc-7b69-471e-9433-9d565be5c338",
      "name": "Sticky Note8",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        768,
        752
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1. This is a table that matches each doctor with their medical speciality.\n\n 2. It is useful for hospitals, clinics, appointment systems, or patient references, so patients can easily identify which doctor to contact for their specific health needs.",
